refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.parameters;




   username



     The Oracle user name.




   password



     The password for username.




   connection_string

    &oci.db;



   character_set

    &oci.charset;



   session_mode

    &oci.sessionmode;

&reftitle.notes;
Starting with PHP 5.1.2 and PECL oci8 1.1, the lifetime and maximum number of persistent Oracle connections can be tuned by setting the following configuration values: oci8.persistent_timeout, oci8.ping_interval and oci8.max_persistent.
In PHP versions before 5.0.0 you must use ociplogon instead. &oci.name.compat.note;
